						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#137;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#141;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#229;&amp;#183;&amp;#165;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#191; (Dowa-fu no Nekkuresu Koubou) can be translated to &amp;quot;The Dwarf Necklace Workshop&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There&amp;rsquo;s always a commotion at the Necklace Workshop where thirteen dwarves work as skilled craftsmen. Even though it&amp;rsquo;s critical that tasks be carried out in a timely manner, the sleepyhead dwarves never rush to get things done. As the proprietress of the workshop, you need to manage the dwarves&amp;rsquo; various abilities in order to produce a beautiful necklace.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of each round, the starting player (who holds the hearth card) selects one dwarf card from the two in their hand and places it so the card is visible to all other players. The remaining players then chose which card they will play from their hand. These cards should be revealed at the same time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the cards have been revealed, the player with the dwarf card of the lowest number gets to go first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, players execute the abilities written on their dwarf card in order from top to bottom in order to build a necklace. After all abilities are executed, the player picks any card from the upper row of cards placed in the middle of the table and adds this card to his or her hand. If there are any jewels on this card, the player also receives them. Then, the player disposes their previously used card into the lower row.&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This ends the player&amp;rsquo;s turn and the next player now starts his or her turn until all players have carried out one turn each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;At the end of the round, one jewel is drawn randomly from the jewel bag and placed onto any card remaining the the upper row in the middle of the table. Then, all cards in the lower round are moved into the upper row so that the row is replenished to a total of 5 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Also at the end the round, the current starting player receives one jewel.&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#168;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player completes stringing 8+ jewels onto their necklace string (6+ in case of a 3 player game), the game proceeds to the final round. The player with the highest valued necklace at the end of the game is the victor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
